Earl Hesterberg Biography

Mr. Earl J. Hesterberg has been and President and Chief Executive Officer of Group 1 Automotive Inc. since April 9, 2005. Mr. Hesterberg served as Group Vice President of North America Marketing, Sales and Service for Ford Motor Co. from October 1, 2004 to April 11, 2005. Prior to joining Group ...
>>Read More 


Mr. Earl J. Hesterberg has been and President and Chief Executive Officer of Group 1 Automotive Inc. since April 9, 2005. Mr. Hesterberg served as Group Vice President of North America Marketing, Sales and Service for Ford Motor Co. from October 1, 2004 to April 11, 2005. Prior to joining Group 1 Automotive, Mr. Hesterberg held various senior executive level sales, marketing, general management, operations, and customer service positions in the United States and Europe with both Ford Motor Company and Nissan Motor Company. He served as Co-Vice President of North America Marketing Sales and Service of Ford Motor Co., a holding company of Ford Motor Credit Co. LLC, since September 10, 2004. Mr. Hesterberg began his Ford career in 1975. In 1982, he moved to Nissan and spent 16 years in various assignments, including Vice President, General Manager of Nissan Division in the U.S. from 1991 to 1995 and later Vice President, Sales, Nissan of Europe. In 1997, Mr. Hesterberg served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Gulf States Toyota, Inc. Mr. Hesterberg returned to Ford in 1999 when he joined Ford of Europe as Vice President of Marketing, Sales & Service. He has been an Executive Director of Group 1 Automotive Inc. since April 2005. He has been a Director of Stage Stores Inc., since July 2010. He serves on the Board of Trustees of Davidson College, and on the Board of Directors of the Greater Houston Partnership. Mr. Hesterberg received his BA in Psychology at Davidson College in 1975 and his MBA from Xavier University in 1978.
